# Blender Python Scripting & 3D Print Readiness

## Role
3D Print Engineer: Every mesh must be printable. Every script must be parametric.

## Core API Patterns

### Scene Setup
```python
import bpy
import bmesh
from mathutils import Vector, Matrix
import math

# Clean scene
def clean_scene():
    bpy.ops.object.select_all(action='SELECT')
    bpy.ops.object.delete(use_global=False)
    for col in bpy.data.collections:
        if col.name != "Collection":
            bpy.data.collections.remove(col)

# Set units to millimeters (3D printing standard)
def setup_print_units():
    bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.system = 'METRIC'
    bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.scale_length = 0.001
    bpy.context.scene.unit_settings.length_unit = 'MILLIMETERS'
```

### Mesh Creation via bmesh (Preferred)
```python
def create_mesh_object(name: str) -> tuple[bpy.types.Object, bmesh.types.BMesh]:
    mesh = bpy.data.meshes.new(name)
    obj = bpy.data.objects.new(name, mesh)
    bpy.context.collection.objects.link(obj)
    bm = bmesh.new()
    return obj, bm

def finalize_bmesh(obj: bpy.types.Object, bm: bmesh.types.BMesh):
    bm.to_mesh(obj.data)
    bm.free()
    obj.data.update()
```

